Morans I

weights <- list(cbg_Q, cbg_R, cbg_kn5, cbg_kn15, cbg_kn30)
weight_name <- list("Queen", "Rook", "knn 5", "knn 15", "knn 30")
Morans_result <- data.frame(weight = character(), Moran_I = numeric(), p_value = numeric()) # dataframe to store results
for (i in seq_along(weights)) {
  x <- moran.test(cbg$CBA12, weights[[i]])
  moran_i <- x$estimate[1]
  p_value <- x$p.value
  Morans_result <- rbind(Morans_result, data.frame(weight = weight_name[[i]], Moran_I = moran_i, p_value = p_value))
}

LISA

This function allows to check hotspots and coldspots with different k values in k-nearest neighbor matrix.

# function
analyze_local_moran <- function(data, variable,id, k) {
  # Load required libraries
  library(spdep)
  tmap_mode("plot")

  # Extract the variable of interest
  var_data <- data[[variable]]
  id_data <- data[[id]]
  coords <- coordinates(data)
  IDs <- row.names(as(data, "data.frame")) 
  # Create neighbor using value of k
  aids_kn <- knn2nb(knearneigh(coords, k = k), row.names = data$IDs) 

  # Make weighted matrix
  aids_kn_w <- nb2listw(aids_kn)

  # LISA
  zips  <-  order(id_data)

  nylocI <- localmoran(var_data, aids_kn_w, alternative = "two.sided")

  # Print results
  #zips <- order(data$ZIPNum)
  #printCoefmat(data.frame(nylocI[zips,], row.names = data$POSTAL[zips]), check.names = TRUE)

  # Plot the clusters
  quadrant <- vector(mode = "numeric", length = nrow(nylocI))

  # Centers the variable of interest around its mean if it's numeric
  if (is.numeric(var_data)) {
    m.sidr <- var_data - mean(var_data)
  } else {
    m.sidr <- var_data - mean(var_data) #rep(0, length(var_data))  # Create a vector of zeros if non-numeric
  }

  # Centers the local Moran's around the mean
  m.local <- nylocI[,1] - mean(nylocI[,1])

  # Significance threshold
  signif <- 0.05 

  # Builds a data quadrant
  quadrant[m.sidr > 0 & m.local > 0] <- 4  # high-high
  quadrant[m.sidr < 0 & m.local < 0] <- 1  # low-low    
  quadrant[m.sidr < 0 & m.local > 0] <- 2  # low-high
  quadrant[m.sidr > 0 & m.local < 0] <- 3  # high-low
  quadrant[nylocI[,5] > signif] <- 0   # not significant
  
  # Convert quadrant to factor
  quadrant <- factor(quadrant, levels = 0:4,
                     labels = c("not significant", "low-low", "low-high", "high-low", "high-high"))
# Add quadrant to data
  data$quadrant <- quadrant
  data$quadrant <- factor(data$quadrant, levels = c("not significant", "low-low", "low-high", "high-low", "high-high"))

  # Create a tmap object
  tm_map <- tm_shape(data) +
    tm_polygons("quadrant", palette = c("white", "blue", "skyblue", rgb(1, 0, 0, alpha = 0.4), "red"), title = variable) +
    tm_borders() +
    tm_layout(legend.position = c(.01, .05),
              legend.bg.color = "white",
              legend.title.fontface = "bold",
              legend.text.fontface = "italic",
              legend.title.size = 1,
              legend.text.size = 0.8,
              legend.frame = FALSE,
              title = "LISA",
              title.position = c("left", "top"),
              title.size = 1.2) +
    tm_scale_bar(position = c(.7,.01), size=.8) +
    tm_compass(size = 3, position = c(.85,.2))

  # Plot using tmap
  tmap_mode("plot")
  print(tm_map)
}

## model diagnostic

analyze_model <- function(m, data) {
  # VIF
  print(vif(m))
  
  # Normality of residual
  residuals <- resid(m)
  dotchart(residuals, xlab = "Residuals")
  
  
  qqnorm(residuals)
  qqline(residuals)
  

  
  print(shapiro.test(residuals))
  print(ks.test(residuals, "pnorm", mean = mean(residuals), sd = sd(residuals)))
  
  # Heteroskedasticity
  yhat <- fitted(m)
  plot(yhat, residuals)
  library(lmtest)
  print(bptest(m))
  
  # OVB
  res <- as.data.frame(residuals)
  data_res <- cbind(data, res)
  plot_correlation(data_res)
  
  # Serial Autocorrelation
  plot(residuals, main="Residuals", ylab="Residuals", type="l")
  
  # Spatial Autocorrelation
  moran.test(cbg$CBA12, weights[[i]])
}
